<div id="content">

  <article>
    <header>
      <h1><a href="/interactive-website">Your Interactive Website</a></h1>
      <p class="postdate">2007-08-18</p>
    </header>

<!-- UPDATE: 2016-02-01 -->
<p>
	Your website can be your best tool, if you make it a two-way communication with your fans and potential fans.
</p><p>
	Your website should get people involved, make them want to introduce themselves, ask questions, shout out.
</p><ol><li>
	Get their email address!
	Interact!
	Make an easy fill-out form.
	(hint: try a fun question like “who are you?” or “do you know your own name?”)
</li><li>
	Encourage them to buy your music, come to a show, or support you in crowdfunding.
	It's a great way to start a relationship.
</li><li>
	Show what's unique about you.
	Image, quirks, colors, moods.
</li><li>
	Make the audio player easy to find.
	Get them listening as soon as possible.
</li><li>
	Answer the obvious questions that first-time visitors have: who are you, what do you look like, what do you sound like.
</li><li>
	Acknowledge them!
	Have their pictures on your site.
	Answer their questions on your site.
	Show them they are a part of your life.
</li></ol><p>
	And make sure you have your own domain name.
</p>
<img src="/images/interactive-website.gif" alt="Your Interactive Website" />


